704685f-a.title: Brooklyn: Grand Street - Bedford Avenue
704685f-a.text:
189-199 9rand Street, north side, between Bedford and Driggs Aves.
S. Woolsey and Sons building, was erected in 1894; the firm was dissolved in
1909. The site was occupied in 1846, by Sewards Dry Goods store, and in
1929 was No. 193 Grand Street.
November 1923.
Eugene L. Anmbruster Collection.
MAY RE REPRODUCED.
